_Earl_of_Lovelace\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:William King-Noel, 1st Earl of Lovelace\">William King</a> in 1835. They became earl and countess of Lovelace in 1838. Ada Lovelace was an avid mathematician and is often called the first computer programmer, after she wrote an algorithm for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Charles_Babbage\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Charles Babbage\">Charles Babbage</a>'s <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytical_Engine\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Analytical Engine\">Analytical Engine</a>.</div>", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "DateTimeOriginal": {"value": "1836 <span class=\"mw-valign-text-top noprint\" typeof=\"mw:File/Frameless\"><a href=\"https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q119052629#P571\" title=\"Edit this at Wikidata\"><img alt=\"Edit this at Wikidata\" src=\"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8a/OOjs_UI_icon_edit-ltr-progressive.svg/20px-OOjs_UI_icon_edit-ltr-progressive.svg.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"10\" height=\"10\" class=\"mw-file-element\" data-file-width=\"20\" data-file-height=\"20\"></a></span>", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "Credit": {"value": "<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://artcollection.culture.gov.uk/artwork/2172/\">UK Government Art Collection website</a>.<br>Original upload was at English wikipedia at <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ada_Lovelace.jpg\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"en:File:Ada Lovelace.jpg\">en:File:Ada_Lovelace.jpg</a>", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "LicenseShortName": {"value": "Public domain", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "UsageTerms": {"value": "Public domain", "source": "commons-desc-page"}, "AttributionRequired": {"value": "false", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "Copyrighted": {"value": "False", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "Restrictions": {"value": "", "source": "commons-desc-page", "hidden": ""}, "License": {"value": "pd", "source": "commons-templates", "hidden":